data.name: dlgUploadExistingData_confirm_upload_rename
data.value:
All files belonging to a project must have a name whose root matches the project name; that is, they must be called ProjectName.xxx. When you start an activity, it will locate the project files by using the project name with an appropriate extension. There are exceptions, such as template and sample files. When you upload a file that has an extension that DimensionNet recognizes as a project file extension, and its name does not match the project name, Files asks you whether you want it to rename the file. You should normally answer Yes to this question.
Do you want to rename the uploaded file "{0}" to a project file called "{1}"?
data.comment: {0} is replaced with the filename of the uploaded file. {1} is replaced with the name the ManageFiles would like to rename the file to
